      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CANADIAN FLING (7) is in a top Sydney stable and presents off an easy and deserved Maiden win this course and distance. She is free running and draws inside again. She has plenty of scope for improvement and can take the next step. ASTROGAZER (4) is a threat building on his 3.3L all-the-way win over 1600m at Orange. Has some weight relief and has more to give. RULE OF FAITH (9) improved again beaten less than 1L at Canberra off a solid effort at Newcastle. Was heavily bet and tackles a middle distance for the first time on a 7-day back-up. Has upside and she deserves plenty of consideration. BURN THE SKY (2) resumed over 1400m at Kembla Grange and needed the outing. Didn't have much luck, regardless, and the blinkers are applied for the first time. She's in a strong metro barn and quick improvement won't surprise.",
